Michael Hansen wrote:

&gt; Hi!
&gt;
&gt; I tried the latest build on XP. I get a new error (did you fix the 
&gt; class path issue St.Ack?). 

I was able to steal some minutes on a windows machine and noticed that 
when I create a new job based on one of the profiles, the order file is 
effectively empty, filled with defaults with key modules completely 
absent (The order file is likely at 
$TOMCAT_HOME/jobs/YOUR_JOB_NAME_TIMESTAMP/order.xml).  Its empty I&#39;m 
guessing because we&#39;re failing to find profiles on the classpath (I 
tried playing with path separator in the location cited in an earlier 
mail but this is not sufficent it seems, need to do more digging).  Is 
your order near-empty too?  Does it look like the attached order.xml or 
is way shorter?

I was able to make things work by overlaying the curtailed order.xml 
with a filled-out order file -- use the attachment as a base -- 
thereafter creating new jobs by basing them off the job that has had the 
overlay applied (A permutation on Subramanya&#39;s suggestion): i.e.

1. Create job based on profile. Lets call the new job, X.
2. Copy the attached order.xml over X&#39;s order file in 
$TOMCAT_HOME/jobs/X-TIMESTAMP/.
3. Restart tomcat (May not be necessary, but do it to be sure).
4. Create new job Y based off X.

Hope this helps.
St.Ack




